                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/240: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-01-02T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 2, 1930—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 3—10:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. Legation’s 1204, December 30, 5 p.m.,<note n="36" xml:id="d434fn36">
                        <ref target="frus1929v02#pg_669">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1929, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 669</ref>.</note> paragraph 2. British
                    Minister left today for Nanking to initiate negotiations having as their aim the
                    gradual relinquishment of British extraterritorial rights.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
